    <title>Refugees contributor: Matthew Goodwin</title>
    <description>Matthew Goodwin is professor of politics at the University of Kent and associate fellow at Chatham House. He is also a senior fellow in the U.K. on a Changing Europe project. His most recent publications include “Revolt on the Right: Explaining Support for the Radical Right in Britain” (Routledge, 2014) and “Brexit: Why Britain Voted to Leave the European Union” (Cambridge University Press, 2017). He tweets as @GoodwinMJ.
